ny and Portugal). If the saint existed at all, he was perhaps martyred in Palestine in the persecutions of Christians instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  at the beginning of the 4th century. The popular legend in which the hero slays a dragon is a medieval Italian invention. He was for a long time a more important saint in the Orthodox Church than in the West, and the name was not much used in England during the Middle Ages, even after  St George  came to be regarded as the patron of England in the 14th century. Its use increased from the 1400s, and by  1500  it was regularly among the most popular male names. This popularity was reinforced when  George I  came to the throne in  1714 , bringing this name with him from Germany. It has been one of the most popular English boys' names ever since."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Georg Moltke was born about 1256, in Germany. He married Unknown about 1290. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1256–":"umbes 1256–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1256–Male":"1256–Surnud","1346":"1346","Abt 1256":"umbes 1256","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1256":"1256","1286":"1286","ABOUT 1286":"umbes 1286","1260":"1260",",,, Germany":"Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1256–":"noin 1256–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1256–Male":"1256–Kuollut","1346":"1346","Abt 1256":"noin 1256","about 1290":"noin 1290","1256":"1256","1286":"1286","ABOUT 1286":"noin 1286","1260":"1260",",,, Germany":"Saksa","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"Abt 1256–":"environ 1256–Décédé","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1256–Male":"1256–Décédé","1346":"1346","Abt 1256":"environ 1256","about 1290":"environ 1290","1256":"1256","1286":"1286","ABOUT 1286":"environ 1286","1260":"1260",",,, Germany":"Allemagne","Germany":"Allemagne","lifeSummary":"Georg Moltke est né environ 1256, à Allemagne. Il a épousé Unknown environ 1290. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1256–":"um 1256–Verstorben